abstract: The progress of railway-building in India continues to be rapid. Much was done during the Afghan war, but the work did not stop with the return of peace. On Jan. 1, 1880, 9,325 miles of road were open, and 838 miles had been added during the year then ended. Compared with the previous year, the increase of net revenue was considerably more than a half-million sterling.

abstract: HONG KONG, Sept. 14.--The construction of the telegraph line from Shanghai to Tientsin is going on satisfactorily. The presence of Government officers and the Government statement of property checked whatever feelings of hostility the natives have felt for such an innovation. The line is expected to be open for business by the end of the year.

abstract: Yachting 20 miles to the windward in a heavy sea is fine sport for yachtsmen, who are not fond of smooth water, but it is not very easy work. abstract: The alterative mineral waters, which constitute our third class, are of great importance. They possess special alterative properties which distinguish them from other water in their effects upon the system. All medicinal waters are less or more alternative in their action. The cathartic and diuretic waters change the action of the system to some extent, but their alterative action is secondary to and in consequence of their primary action.

abstract: SChiller and  Goethe gave the crowning grace to Germany's poetic glory. There was little poetry immediately before them; there has been little since.
